# Blade form fields

## Explicit bind only (no `old()`)

- **Do not** use **`old()`**, **`old('...')`**, **`@if (old(...))`**, or **`data_get(old(...))`** in Blade for **`value`**, **`selected`**, **`checked`**, or any conditional on repopulated input. Bind from **route model** fields (e.g. **`$user->email`** on edit), **named variables** the controller passes (e.g. **`$name ?? ''`**), or **Livewire** / **Inertia**-style props.
- **Create** forms without a model: use **empty** defaults (e.g. **`value=""`**, **`value="1"`** where fixed default), first **empty** `<option>`, and **unchecked** checkboxes unless the domain requires otherwise.
- Keep views aligned with **Livewire / SPA** navigation and a single source of truth from the server (no session-field repopulation in Blade for failed validation).

- Wrap each **logical field** (or one **translatable / repeated field group**) in a Blade comment **immediately above** the outermost markup for that field: `{{--field_key--}}`.
- Use a short, stable key (usually the main `name` attribute or domain concept): e.g. `{{--name--}}`, `{{--email--}}`, `{{--password--}}`. Do **not** add a field comment for **submit** `<button>` elements (primary Save/Submit, delete, confirm, etc.)—they are not marked with `{{--submit--}}` or any similar key.
- Keys use **snake_case** when multiple words are needed (e.g. `{{--start_date--}}`).
- One comment per field **block**: the comment opens the section; the closing `</div>` / row does not need a matching closing comment.
- For `@foreach` over languages (or similar), put **one** `{{--name--}}` (or `{{--code--}}`) above the **row** that contains the loop, not inside each iteration.
- **`autofocus` in `@foreach` over languages (or similar)**: If a text `<input>` should receive initial focus and uses **`autofocus`**, apply it **only on the first iteration**: **`{{ $loop->first ? 'autofocus' : '' }}`** (ternary in `{{ }}`, same style as optional `disabled` / `checked`). Do **not** output the bare **`autofocus`** attribute on every iteration—only one control may be focused, and duplicate **`autofocus`** is invalid / unpredictable.
- The field wrapper may use **`form-group`** (Bootstrap 4) or **`mb-3`** (Bootstrap 5) for vertical spacing—match the Bootstrap version and patterns already used in that view. **`form-group`** supplies spacing for that field; **`mb-3`** is the B5 substitute when you are **not** using **`form-group`** on that block.
- **`form-group` and `mb-3` are mutually exclusive in the same field hierarchy**: **never** add **`mb-3`** anywhere (same element, a parent **`col-*`**, **`row`**, or any other wrapper between `{{--key--}}` and the control) when a **`form-group`** wraps the **`input`**, **`select`**, **`textarea`**, or the usual **`label` + control** group for that field. Use plain **`col-*`** (e.g. **`col-md-6`**) without **`mb-3`** when **`form-group`** sits inside the column. For a **standalone** field with no `row`/`col-*`, the outer wrapper is either **`form-group`** or **`mb-3`**, not both—the ✖ examples below apply to that case too. The `{{--key--}}` comment stays directly above that outer field wrapper (whether it is `form-group`, `mb-3`, or a `row` that groups multiple columns; see grid rule below).
- **Grid (`row` / `col-*`)**:
    - **Anti-pattern**: a `<div class="row">` whose **only** field block is a single `col-*` wrapper (including `col-12`)—redundant grid; use `form-group` or `mb-3` directly under the `{{--key--}}` comment. This is **not** a ban on `col-12` in every situation.
    - **Valid**: `col-12` inside a `row` that also has **other** `col-*` siblings (e.g. `col-md-6` + `col-md-6` + `col-12` in one flex row) when you intentionally mix full-width and split columns in the same row.
    - **Preferred** for full-width fields **between** multi-column groups: **close** the `row` after the last field that shares that row with other `col-*` siblings; put full-width fields in **`form-group`** or **`mb-3`** (one or the other, not both) **outside** the `row` **without** `col-*`; **open a new `row`** when the next section has two or more columns again.
    - Use `row` + `col-*` when there are **two or more** fields on the same row, or when the view already uses a multi-column layout for that section.
- **Blank line before the comment**: If the line immediately above the `{{--key--}}` comment is not blank (e.g. a parent opening tag like `<div class="row ...">`, or closing markup from a sibling), insert **one blank line** before the Blade comment so each field block is visually separated. Do not stack the comment directly under non-blank markup without that spacer.
- **Submit-only / minimal forms** (delete, confirm, icon-only): Do **not** add a field comment above the `<form>` when it only contains `@csrf`, `@method(...)`, and submit button(s)—same as above: submit actions are never labeled with `{{--submit--}}`.
- **Date fields**: always add the **`date-picker`** class on the input together with **`form-control`** (e.g. `class="form-control date-picker"`), whether the input is `type="date"`, `type="text"`, or whatever the view stack uses for the shared date-picker behavior.
- **Time fields**: always add the **`time-picker`** class on the input together with **`form-control`** (e.g. `class="form-control time-picker"`) for the shared time-picker behavior.
- **Date range fields** (start/end in one control or paired range UX): always add the **`date-range-picker`** class on the input together with **`form-control`** (e.g. `class="form-control date-range-picker"`).
- **Select fields**: always add the **`select2`** class on `<select>` together with **`form-control`** (e.g. `class="form-control select2"`) for the shared Select2 behavior—form dropdowns, index filters, and any other `<select>`.
- **Conditional attributes on elements** (`disabled`, `readonly`, `checked`, `selected`, etc.): Do **not** use Blade `@if` / `@elseif` / `@endif` **inside** an opening tag (e.g. `<select ... @if (! $foo) disabled @endif>`). Use a **ternary** inside `{{ }}` so the attribute is one expression: e.g. `{{ $condition ? 'disabled' : '' }}`, `{{ $condition ? 'readonly' : '' }}`, `{{ $condition ? 'checked' : '' }}`—same idea as the lone-checkbox `checked` example below. Do **not** split the tag with inline `@if` for a single optional attribute.
- **Index pages with DataTable** (filter row above a server-side DataTable / `table.datatable`): Do **not** add a `<label>` above filter controls. Use **`placeholder`** on the search input (e.g. `@lang('site.search')`). For **`<select>`** filters, convey meaning with the **first `<option>`** (the “all / no filter” row)—often `value="0"` when the backend treats `0` as omitted, with text like `@lang('site.all')` plus the domain noun when it reads clearly (e.g. `@lang('site.all') @lang('tags.tags')`); align `value` and AJAX `data` with what controllers and `scopeWhen*` / `when()` treat as “no filter”. Match **other admin `index.blade.php`** files that use the same DataTable filter pattern in this project. **Filter `row` utilities**: reuse the same **`class`** on the filter wrapper **`row`** as **peer** index views in the same app area (e.g. **`resources/views/admin/`** vs nursery)—most use plain **`row`**; add **`mb-4`**, **`align-items-end`**, or other spacing only when those peers do for the same card section. **Do not** treat a fixed combo from examples below (e.g. **`row mb-4 align-items-end`**) as required if it diverges from the rest of the index pages.
- **Enum- or constant-backed filter `<select>` options** (e.g. status): Use `@foreach` with an inline array of class constants when you need a fixed display order; alternatively use sorted `SomeEnum::getConstants()` (or similar) for a single source of truth, accepting that reflection order is undefined unless you sort. For option labels, when the entity lang file defines keys like `status_active`, `status_inactive`, use `__('entity.status_' . strtolower($value))` (keep **`strtolower()`** when stored values might be mixed case). The first segment of the translation key must still match the entity file—see **blade-translation**.

